<h1>
  <span>4.</span> Request Header Details:</h1>
<ul>
  <li data-uuid="a113beec-7adf-4d83-9b84-dcd250476004">User should fill in all the mandatory fields which are marked with the red colour asterisk symbol (*) and until all mandatory fields are entered, next button should be disabled.</li>
</ul>
<p style="margin-left: 40.0px;">
  <ac:image ac:height="239">
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-39-28-1.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<ul>
  <li data-uuid="40e53943-c952-4262-b7b4-294d0a0ff885">Contact Name &amp; Account Name will be auto populated as Hyperlinks. The selected Service Type is shown as the text field.</li>
  <li data-uuid="92e9c1a1-9188-4047-aeba-b992f329e33f">
    <strong>Sold To: </strong>All the ‘Customer CMF’ records which are related to the account which have a related ‘Customer Partner’ record (with role code : AG) can be selected as valid sold to.</li>
  <li data-uuid="5301d2fe-a4ce-494e-9819-ba7794a04413">For selecting Sold To, we have a wild card search functionality which makes it easy to search and get the required CMF value instead of going through all the values in a dropdown.</li>
  <li data-uuid="85d25bc8-6760-40b6-adc9-974948ace494">Based on the Selected Sold To Value, all other data will be fetched for other dropdowns.</li>
  <li data-uuid="e85b4eda-082a-4458-bbfe-010b98a77fcb">When Sold To is selected, all the other details are auto populated based on the selected ‘Sold to’ value. Values are auto populated based on the most recent case created using that particular ‘Sold To’ if there is historical data of case being created using that Sold To CMF.</li>
  <li data-uuid="0be6a4ea-9984-4806-800e-c6f16a97b1f7">All other fields in Request header details are dropdowns, if any dropdown contains a single value, it would be auto populated when agent selects a value on dependent dropdown for that dropdown.</li>
