  </span>
</p>
<ul>
  <li data-uuid="4ce99079-90cc-40c2-8cd9-32299686a3ce">To see the address records related to selected Sold To: Go to the sold to ‘Customer CMF record’ &gt; Open the Related tab &gt; Customer Physical Addresses &gt; See the address Type as ‘Return To Customer’. All the active address records would be displayed for agent to choose from.</li>
  <li data-uuid="21e9ddc6-5cca-42dd-b1e3-245f2ae26778">
    <span> </span>
    <span>
      <strong>Return to Customer Contact</strong>
    </span>
    <span>: These contact values are fetched based on the selected ‘Return to Customer Address. </span>
  </li>
  <li data-uuid="3ae93453-7b4a-471c-9746-843e71b73065">To see the contact records related to selected <span>‘Return to Customer Address’</span>: Go to the sold to ‘Customer CMF record’ &gt; Open the Related tab &gt; Customer Physical Addresses &gt; Open the selected ‘Return To Customer’ address record &gt; Open the Related tab &gt; Physical Address Contacts. All the active contact records would be displayed for agents to choose from.</li>
  <li data-uuid="fdf2c731-665a-4aa8-bf78-9a7f350ed0d1">
    <strong>Freight Type: </strong>Once ‘Return to Customer Address’ is selected, Freight type values are determined and populated from <strong>‘Sales Freight Determination Matrix’</strong>.<ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Sales Freight Determination Matrix: </strong>Freight Determination<strong> </strong>is fetched from matrix based on below parameters, record from the matrix with least priority number and matching criteria is fetched<ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Service Type</strong>
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Remedy Type</strong>
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Country</strong>
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Return Reason</strong>
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Geography</strong>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li>The values are populated from filtering the matrix records by passing Remedy, Service Type, Return Reason, Geo, Country (RTC Address Country) fields in the matrix. If no record is found, we exclude Country and fetch the record. If still no record is found, we exclude Return Reason and fetch the record.<ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Freight Type-IMF (Intel Managed Freight):</strong>
            <ul>
              <li>If the customer selects the freight type as IMF (Intel Managed Freight), then all collection details fields are mandatory to proceed further.</li>
              <li>After selecting the Collection Address, the collection date field is enabled, and date is auto populated.</li>
              <li>
                <strong>Collection Date</strong> is auto populated based on <strong>Geo Lead Time Matrix</strong> for IMF.</li>
              <li>For APAC / APJ - 5 days are considered as ‘Lead Time’. Here the 5<sup>th</sup> day from current day/ case creation day will be auto populated in the collection date. Apart from that the 4<sup>th</sup> day would be enabled for Customer to choose from and the next 8 days would also be enabled for a total of 10 enabled days. These dates are all excluding holidays and weekends.</li>
              <li>For all other regions – ‘Lead Time’ is 3 days. Therefore, 3<sup>rd</sup> day from current day would be auto populated, 2<sup>nd</sup> day would be enabled along with the next 8 days succeeding ‘Lead Time’ excluding holidays &amp; weekends.</li>
              <li>Example- Let Case creation date is 14<sup>th</sup> Mar 2023, the date auto populated for Geo APJ would be 22<sup>nd</sup> Mar 2023 if there is no holiday for the selected collection Address. If there is holiday for that country on 22<sup>nd</sup> Mar 2023, then it would be auto populated as 23<sup>rd</sup> Mar 2023.</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ul>
<p>
  <br/>
</p>
<ul>
  <li data-uuid="4f7f720e-774c-4bd8-b374-5d7c8d8a623e">
    <strong>Incoterm Determination:</strong>
  </li>
</ul>
<p style="margin-left: 40.0px;"> When freight type is IMF, Incoterm value is determined by checking for the exact matching record by passing Remedy, Service Type, Return Reason, Geo, Country(Collection Address Country) fields to ‘Incoterm Determination Matrix’. If no record is found, we exclude Country and fetch the record. If still no record is found, we exclude Return Reason and fetch the record.</p>
<ul>
