</p>
<h1>
  <strong> Email Approval Scenario:</strong>
</h1>
<ul>
  <li data-uuid="89fe5c89-3603-4d4c-b2be-2428e9fee1da">Price Override Scenarios:<ul>
      <li>If total price overridden for line items is greater than 25k and Net Credit value is greater than 100k, then first ‘L3 Approver’ needs to approve the particular line items before case is sent to External approver.</li>
      <li>If L3 approver declines the approval request, then Case status is set to ‘Declined’ and external approval will not be triggered.</li>
      <li>If L3 approver approves the approval request, another email will be triggered to external approver, based on his response the case status gets updated to ‘RMA Authorized’ or ‘Declined’.</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li data-uuid="56da87b0-2ae9-4224-901a-0bf4375d3c70">In case of price override less than 25k and Net Credit value is greater than 100k, on load of ‘View Summary page’, email of external approver is fetched from ‘Approval Matrix’ by sending sold to CMF, remedy, return reason, service type, distribution channel and sales org along with net credit price.</li>
  <li data-uuid="4e15e470-6028-488c-9723-e0b36ccdff74">On click of ‘Submit’ button, case status is set to ‘Pending Approval’ and email is sent to approver for approval, based on his response the case status gets updated to ‘RMA Authorized’ or ‘Declined’..</li>
  <li data-uuid="231935f2-c9d1-4630-add1-614ad86f6571">If no approver record is found, agent is notified by error toast message.</li>
</ul>
<p>
  <br/>
</p>
<p>Note:</p>
<ul>
  <li data-uuid="7c6a384e-bbfb-480a-9d16-354d10d81654">Onclick of submit button if there are any failed line items in the case process those line items will be triggered an email to CQE with the error message.</li>
  <li data-uuid="996681ef-827e-496f-9219-c7262cda3690">Once the case status gets ‘RMA Authorized’, an email will be triggered to CQE and Agent, regarding shipping instructions information.</li>
  <li data-uuid="4b689a40-a84e-4ef8-a5bf-488aa01f0e55">
    <strong>For Draft cases,</strong> we check SAP Blocks on Load when the Edit R4C button is clicked, and if any hard blocks existing or if any inactive records are part of case, then it’s a hard stop and Agents can’t edit the case else if no blocks and no inactive CMFs Agent can edit Collection details as well as Line Items</li>
  <li data-uuid="8d22f88b-7246-4b83-8aa3-508f802ecc1d">The Default landing page for the line items is Search/Upload Line Items Page, line items can be deleted by using dropdown or unselect the line items, in the data base, the line items status gets set to Deleted.<ul>
      <li>
        <u>Cancel Line Items:</u>
      </li>
      <li>In Edit Case tab, we have an additional column ‘Line items status’ where agent can select to delete line items.</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ul>
